body:
Just finished Season 2, episode 3.

I don’t like Anai, lil’ trouble-maker!

But they just showed Donkey Boy (don’t know his name yet) and he looks sweet!

I’m still team Haida, but I’m assuming Retsuko is gonna end up liking this guy? And if so, not sure I can hate him???

We’ll see!!!

Ps, her mom need to lay off! (Why is she randomly showing up at Retsuko’s house every day now anyway?!)

On to episode 4!

tags: Which the one thing that comes to mind is universal income again
summary:
After watching 
aggretsuko s2. I’d say it would be nice to live in a world where -creatives- have more time and resources to...
body:
After watching aggretsuko s2. I’d say it would be nice to live in a world where -creatives- have more time and resources to make their dreams reality, and not everyone is up for that type of life! I had similar thinking to Tadano’s thought process for a little while, believing not wanting to work would be something everyone would want…till I realized there are alot of people out there still that love to work and it’s a part of their life, and I realized that a few years ago talking to people older than me.

There are alot of people out there suffering from the current work climate, pay wise, health wise, and creative wise, and there are those that are quite happy at their jobs! It would be nice to work towards a goal that benefits both ends of that spectrum.
